.TH "pci_release_region" 9 "pci_release_region" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
pci_release_region \- Release a PCI bar
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" pci_release_region
.BI "(struct pci_dev *pdev "  ","
.BI "int bar "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "pdev" 12
PCI device whose resources were previously reserved by
\fBpci_request_region\fP
.IP "bar" 12
BAR to release
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Releases the PCI I/O and memory resources previously reserved by a
successful call to \fBpci_request_region\fP.  Call this function only
after all use of the PCI regions has ceased.
